Tomcat 4+, with administrative applications installed
PostgreSQL 7.4.2+ with contribs installed
JDK 1.4.1+

For Debian users:

1) apt-get install tomcat4 tomcat4-admin postgresql postgresql-contrib

2) One of the following:
	a) 'apt-get install j2sdk1.4' to use Blackdown's Java, or
	b) 'apt-get install java-package', download the 1.4.2 JDK from Sun's
	   web site, and run make-jpkg on the .bin file you downloaded. This
	   gives you a file named 'sun-j2sdk1.4.deb'. Do 'apt-get install
	   sun-j2sdk1.4debian', then 'dpkg -i sun-j2sdk1.4.deb'.
